Why Should You Buy Maruti Suzuki Victoris? Know 5 reasons

Maruti Suzuki is back with one more impressive and compelling model, Victoris, to expand its SUV portfolio in India. The Maruti Suzuki Victoris is launched to take on strong competitors in the segment, such as the Hyundai Creta and Kia Seltos. The company unveiled the compact SUV with a special slogan, ‘Got it all,’ which has generated considerable curiosity among Maruti fans and car enthusiasts. We reviewed it and found 5 impressive features that you must know. Also, if you are planning to buy it, you can check out a brand-new range of Maruti Suzuki Victoris accessories at our store to amplify its safety and comfort and to add a personal statement. What Are The 5 Pros of Maruti Suzuki Victoris? · Strikingly new look and design The first thing that you will notice about all Maruti Victoris models is their contemporary look and design. By far, it’s the sleekest and boldest Maruti car launched in the budget segment. It appears that the European-styled vehicle has been launched in India, featuring bold and sleek LED taillights and a closed grille.   · On-road comfort Comfort is yet another important feature that most buyers consider when purchasing a new car. Maruti Victoris registered a victory in this department by offering a comfortable drive in this segment. The fine suspension tuning is felt while driving on city potholes and major stretches. It gives a cushioned feeling to passengers when it’s on the road.   · Tech-driven cabin When it comes to technology, Maruti Suzuki Victoris offers the best in the segment. One can find out the most popular and trending technology-driven features, with some exclusive ones such as the Smart Pro X system, a complete digital driver’s display, Alexa compatibility, 64-colour ambient lighting, a panoramic sunroof, and many more.   · Premium Infinity audio experience A car is incomplete without an immersive and premium audio system. This is one of the most important and stress-busting features for drivers stuck in long city traffic jams. Considering the need of the hour, Maruti Suzuki Victoris brings the Dolby Atmos-driven Infinity sound system, which offers amazing sound quality, surround effect, and immersive experience to drivers.   · 5-star BNCAP and GNCAP rating If you are looking for the safest Maruti Suzuki car, then the Maruti Victoris is the best one to consider. The car offers a 5-star GNCAP and BNCAP rating along with the flagship Level 2 ADAS and premium safety features. Many people complain about the safety standards of the Maruti cars. But, with Victoris, the company has taken a giant leap by putting a complete focus on safety parameters.   What Are The 5 Cons Of The Maruti Suzuki Victoris? Every coin has two sides. Every car comes with certain limitations due to various factors, including pricing, materials used, design, and aerodynamics. Similarly, the Maruti Suzuki Victor also has some aspects that may turn you off. However, these cons are unable to outnumber its pros. · Highway instability The car offers an excellent driving experience in the city. However, when you take it to a highway, it starts showing instability. Over 110 km/h, the steering starts to shiver, and smoothness goes out of the window. It feels a little risky to take sharp turns. · The use of plastic in the interior Although the cabin is laced with tech-driven features, you can clearly find out the plastic use in some areas, including the drive mode selector, parking brake, etc. It may turn off some buyers. · Brake instability When it comes to the braking performance, the car shows a little inconsistency and instability. The emergency stops may cause some discomfort to drivers. It’s not as strong as other SUVs in the segment. It could have been stronger.   How To Add A Personalised Touch To Maruti Suzuki Victoris? A new car always brings a lot of excitement and joy. Every customer tries their best to add a personalized touch to spruce up the style, safety, and comfort. To help you with it, AutoFurnish brings a premium custom fit as well as a universal range of Maruti Suzuki Victoris accessories. · Custom-fit premium car foot mats You can adorn your car with our exclusive premium range of custom-fit 9D and 7D Maruti Suzuki Victoris car floor mats. These mats offer advanced safety features and premium design and come in dual-tone colours to take the style and safety quotient to the next level. If you like a rugged look, then pick LTM car foot mats. · Custom-fit body covers We offer an imported range of all-weatherproof Maruti Suzuki Victoris body covers to protect the car’s shine and paint from bird droppings, tree sap, scratches, and harmful UV rays. The premium colours add a distinct look to your car in the parking area. · Seat organizers To prepare in advance, you can pick premium 3D PU leatherette-made car seat organizers to keep the clutter away from your car seats. · Visor tissue box holders Add a visor tissue box holder to your brand new Maruti Suzuki Victoris to create a personalised and stylish look. · Car cushions You can pick stylish and lumbar-support-inducing car seat cushions to give support to your neck, back, and shoulders while driving daily.   Final Wrap: Should you buy Maruti Suzuki Victoris? Yes, you can definitely buy Maruti Suzuki Victoris, as it brings a fresh new European design, a bold look, premium interiors, an unmatched audio experience, and a 5-star safety rating. It looks nothing short of a premium compact SUV that everyone from all walks of life can love driving. And to elevate the driving experience, add explore our premium collection of Maruti Suzuki Victoris accessories.
